description.narrative:
Monitor communicable diseases trends, timely detect outbreaks and effectively respond to all outbreaks including Ebola and other hemorrhagic fevers; 
Monitor neglected tropical disease trends, timely detect and respond to outbreaks including Leishmaniasis (Kala Azar, Leprosy and Schistosomiasis (S. haematobium);

Monitor trends of non communicable diseases in target populations and ensure access to life saving medicines and supplies including for hypertension and diabetes mellitus
Ensure adequate prepositioning and access to effective supplies for outbreak detection or confirmation and case management all zones;
Conduct capacity building activities for health workers including at least 50% female staff where possible and partners including those running cholera treatment centers and during response to unusual health events;
Ensure screening at points of entries is done at designated centers including airport in light of public health emergencies of international concern especially Ebola, Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MersCov)
Ensure adequate pre-positioning of recommended PPEs for Ebola response and Infectious Samples collection and transportation supplies
